    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Prices that are established for certain goods or services and cannot be negotiated. Examples are fixed prices for a certain meal on a restaurant menu, prices set at a bazaar where it is otherwise customary to haggle a lower price, or prices for a market commodity that are set rather than flutuating based on demand.</Note_Text>
